Annie Idibia, the wife of popular singer Tubaba has expressed delight with working with her long-time lover and husband on his new music video ‘Smile’. The popular actress made this known in a post on her verified Instagram page while promoting her husband’s new song in which she was used as the video vixen. The screen diva took a trip down memory lane as she revisited how she became the lead vixen in the African Queen music video about 19 years ago. She mentioned at the time, the singer born Innocent Idibia was known as Tuface.   Skiibii tops music chart with Davido-assisted remix     Son of Hollywood actress Regina King commits suicide     I would be bringing a lot to Nigerian Idol 7- IK Osakioduwa   - Advertisement - Part of her post reads: “19 years Ago … while still struggling to find my feet in the modeling industry, my then boyfriend who just broke from a boy band group called me to starr in his new song (African Queen) we both had no idea the song would change the entire music scene in Africa and it’s narrative and also become the biggest song out of the continent. “Fast forward to 19years later…. and almost 10years married to that amazing rare human ..artist … we get to do this again!!!! it’s #smileseason guys!! I hope this song and visuals by @ryguysa makes you smile. In the spirit of this #smileseason I am feeling generous this evening.. I would like to make a family smile this weekend.. any suggestions.” The smashing hit song, African Queen was released under Kennis Music in 2004. Ever since the release of the song, it has earned the singer and the record company numerous awards.